programme.desc: The Bikers take everyday ingredients and transform them into comforting dishes that are both satisfying and surprising. Bananas are transformed into a sophisticated tarte tatin, and some simple ricotta cheese is the basis for gnudi - light, delicious Italian dumplings.

programme.title: The Pioneer Woman
programme.desc: Ree Drummond refreshes, or Ree-freshes, some of her favourite eats. She makes delicious Skirt Steak and Sweet Potato Fries, rustles up a Tex-Mex Chicken Pot Pie, bakes a Boozy Berry Upside Down Cake and fries up Pesto Egg Toast.

programme.title: The Pioneer Woman
programme.desc: Ree Drummond is cooking dishes that are both simple and refined, starting with Crab Cakes and 5-Ingredient Remoulade; Peppercorn-Crusted Steak with Pimento Creamed Spinach and Lemon-Thyme Sheet Pan Chicken and Potatoes.

programme.title: Jamie Oliver: Together
programme.desc: Jamie creates a super-relaxed menu and cooks up a dynamite Mexican taco night of slow-cooked pork belly with red cabbage slaw, followed by a chocolate semifreddo decked with brittle.

programme.title: Barefoot Contessa

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: In the third series, the search for Britains best amateur baker is back as 12 passionate baking fans compete for the title. Mel Giedroyc and Sue Perkins return as presenters, as do judges Mary Berry and Paul Hollywood, who devise the three challenges faced by the competitors each week. They incorporate a signature bake, which tests the bakers personality and creative flair; a technical bake, which tests experience; and a showstopper bake, during which the bakers are able to showcase their depth of skill and talent. Berry and Hollywood inspect, prod and sample the baked goodies as they decide who gets to have their cake - and eat it.

programme.title: James Martins American Adventure

James arrives on a boat through the bay before cooking on the great historic warship the SS Jeremiah OBrien. James then takes a walk on foot through San Franciscos famous Chinatown and explores the many food stores offering unusual ingredients to the thousands of shoppers that visit every day.

programme.title: James Martins American Adventure
programme.desc: A trip to California wouldnt be complete without a visit to the famous vineyards of Sonoma County. James Martin continues his American Adventure with a drive on his much-loved Harley Davidson to visit a unique winery and farm where he cooks two beautiful dishes using local ingredients. James also visits Single Thread, a farm and restaurant run by a passionate husband and wife team where he is totally overwhelmed by the culinary offerings.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives
programme.desc: Guy Fieris cruisin California for some West Coast wonders. In Healdsburg, a rooftop is creating a charcuterie cornucopia, and in San Diego, a funky joint is dishing out a taste of New Orleans while a breakfast/lunch spot is going sweet and savoury.

programme.title: Diners, Drive-Ins and Dives

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Top BBC chefs are on a mission to popularise traditional British produce. In this first episode, Michel Roux Jr campaigns for the return of the artisan baker to the UK high street and shares his own unique recipes to show how easy and rewarding home baking can be. Next, the Hairy Bikers are on the case of the British cauliflower, determined to show that not only is it nutritious, but versatile and tasty.

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Chef James Martin is reviving the British apple. Forced off the supermarket shelves by identikit fruit that have been shipped in from as far away as New Zealand and Chile, James is determined to show off the qualities of home-grown apples. Chef Matt Tebbutt is on the case of mutton. Due to cheap imports of lamb, mutton has lost its place as a family staple, but Matt is determined to win back its reputation.

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Ainsley Harriott starts a campaign for the revival of British honey. With bees under threat from disease and a lack of awareness of our native honey production, Ainsley finds out how we can all play our part in its revival. Then its time for Michelin starred chef Glynn Purnell to ride to the rescue of British cheese. Cheap foreign imports and misleading labelling means that Glynn has his work cut out for him.

programme.title: Great British Food Revival
programme.desc: Gary Rhodes wants us all to appreciate the virtues of the British tomato. Unlike the Italian and Spanish, we view the tomato as a year round product and ignore the British growing season when our own fruit is at its best. Elsewhere, Angela Hartnett looks at why crab is so unloved in Britain, when our coastal waters are teeming with sweet tasting brown and spider crab.
